        },
        {
            "text": "Although based on limited evidence [11, 12] guidelines suggest performing PCR and CT-scan for asymptomatic patients, preferably 48 hours before surgery. We fear that suggested preference of CT-scan -testing with significantly higher sensitivity [11, 13, 14] might become the bottleneck of pre-operative screening due to limited capacity in the future [15, 16].",
            "cite_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 36,
                    "end": 38,
                    "mention": "11",
                    "ref_id": "BIBREF10"
